rland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":76,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":85,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Alice De Breton was born in 1139, in England. She had at least 1 son with Roger FitzReinfrid."},"et":{"1139–":"1139–Surnud","1144–1187":"1144–1187","1185–1220":"1185–1220","1139–Female":"1139–Surnud","1139":"1139","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1144":"1144","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1185":"1185","about 1185":"umbes 1185","England":"England"},"fi":{"1139–":"1139–Kuollut","1144–1187":"1144–1187","1185–1220":"1185–1220","1139–Female":"1139–Kuollut","1139":"1139","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1144":"1144","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1185":"1185","about 1185":"noin 1185","England":"England"},"fr":{"1139–":"1139–Décédée","1144–1187":"1144–1187","1185–1220":"1185–1220","1139–Female":"1139–Décédée","1139":"1139","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1144":"1144","1220":"1220","1187":"1187","1185":"1185","about 1185":"environ 1185","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice 